What you can truly be ♪

01:37.306 --> 01:42.477
♪ Shining star come into view ♪
¿Cómo está usted?
Yo me Ilamo Guillermo.

01:42.561 --> 01:45.688
[In Unison]
¿Cómo está usted?
Yo me Ilamo Guillermo.

01:45.773 --> 01:48.941
[Spanish]

01:49.026 --> 01:53.279
[Repeating Spanish In Unison]

01:53.363 --> 01:55.031
[Mr. Schue]
Bueno. Bueno.

01:55.115 --> 01:57.575
- ♪ Shining star
for you to see ♪
- [Bell Ringing]

01:57.659 --> 02:00.036
♪ What your life
can truly be ♪♪

02:00.120 --> 02:02.830
♪♪ [Piano]

02:03.832 --> 02:07.585
♪ Where is love ♪

02:07.669 --> 02:09.587
♪ Is love ♪

02:09.713 --> 02:15.468
♪ Does it fall
from skies above ♪
♪ Ooh ♪

02:15.552 --> 02:18.554
♪ Is it underneath ♪

02:18.639 --> 02:21.140
♪ The willow tree ♪

02:21.225 --> 02:27.647
♪ That I've been dreaming of♪

02:32.486 --> 02:35.071
[Bell Ringing]
[Mr. Schue]
Where's the coffeepot?

02:35.155 --> 02:37.323
Figgins got rid of it.
Budget cuts.

02:37.407 --> 02:40.785
You know, I know for a fact
that they are still getting
hot java at Carver.

02:40.869 --> 02:43.663
We should strike.

02:43.747 --> 02:46.707
Hello, boys.
Who needs a pick-me-up?

02:46.792 --> 02:49.210
- Wow. Lattes.
- Yeah. I'm a bit of a coffee snob.

02:49.294 --> 02:52.213
Now, the key
to a perfect latte...

02:52.297 --> 02:54.632
is in the temperature
of the steamed milk.

02:54.716 --> 02:56.425
- I like mine scalding.
- Wow.

02:56.510 --> 02:58.344
- Hi, Emma.
- Hey, Ken.

02:58.428 --> 03:00.930
- Will, hi.
- Hey.

03:01.014 --> 03:04.684
- What's with all the lattes?
- Oh, Emma,
I just felt so awful...

03:04.768 --> 03:08.271
that Figgins cut
the coffee budget to pay for a
nutritionist for the "Cheerios."

03:08.355 --> 03:11.732
Yeah. I heard you guys
went, like, $600
over budget on that.

03:11.817 --> 03:16.153
My performers didn't get on
Fox Sports Net last year because
they ate at Bacon Junction.

03:16.238 --> 03:18.489
Since when are
cheerleaders performers?

03:19.825 --> 03:23.828
Your resentment
is delicious.

03:23.912 --> 03:26.539
Well, I have a "phoner"
in a couple minutes—

03:26.623 --> 03:29.333
That's an interview on the telephone
with a major media outlet.

03:29.418 --> 03:32.003
[Chuckling]
I'll probably do it
on my iPhone.

03:32.129 --> 03:36.090
Enjoy.
Thanks a lot, Sue.

03:38.135 --> 03:40.094
I missed you at the, uh,

03:40.178 --> 03:41.762
singles mixer
last weekend, Emma.

03:41.847 --> 03:44.432
Yeah, I know.
A big pipe exploded
in my building.

03:44.516 --> 03:46.976
It was wild. I hate
those mixer things though.
Don't you?

03:47.060 --> 03:49.770
I mean,
it's like a big meat market.
It's just— Ew.

03:49.855 --> 03:51.814
I did give my number
to a fireman though.

03:51.899 --> 03:53.900
But he hasn't called.

03:53.984 --> 03:56.402
There's someone
out there for everyone.
I wouldn't even sweat it.

03:56.486 --> 04:00.406
[Plastic Bag Tearing]

04:00.490 --> 04:04.368
Mmm. Hey, did you hear
that Sandy Ryerson got fired?

04:04.494 --> 04:08.205
Really?
Mm-hmm.

04:08.290 --> 04:10.666
- Who's gonna
take over Glee Club?
- I don't know.

04:13.253 --> 04:14.629
I'd like to
take over Glee Club.

04:14.713 --> 04:16.172
You want to captain
the Titanic too?

04:16.256 --> 04:19.759
I think I can
make it great again.
There is no joy in these kids.

04:19.843 --> 04:22.553
They feel invisible.
That's why every one of them
has a MySpace page.

04:22.638 --> 04:26.641
Sixty bucks a month.
That's what I need
to keep this program up.

04:26.725 --> 04:28.684
A-A-And you—
you expect me to pay it?

04:28.769 --> 04:30.770
Well, I'm certainly not
going to pay for it.

04:30.854 --> 04:33.940
We're not talking
about Cheerios here, Will.

04:34.024 --> 04:36.150
They were on Fox Sports Net
last year.

04:36.234 --> 04:39.278
When Glee Club starts
bringing that kind
of prestige to the school again,

04:39.363 --> 04:40.863
you can have all
the money you want.

04:40.948 --> 04:42.490
Until then,
60 bucks a month,

04:42.574 --> 04:45.785
and you've got to use
the costumes and props
we already have.

04:45.869 --> 04:49.330
- But we need the stools
for wood shop.
- [Bell Ringing]

04:51.124 --> 04:54.627
[Narrating] Hiding the $60
a month from my wife, Terri,
was gonna be hard.

04:54.711 --> 04:59.131
But I had a bigger problem.
How was I gonna
get these kids motivated?

04:59.216 --> 05:01.759
One thing I knew for sure—
we needed a new name.

05:01.843 --> 05:04.887
New Directions!

05:04.972 --> 05:07.765
[Bell Ringing]

05:07.849 --> 05:10.393
My name is Mercedes Jones,
and I'm singing—

05:10.477 --> 05:14.480
♪ R-E-S-P-E-C-T
Find out what it means to me ♪

05:14.564 --> 05:18.693
♪ R-E-S-P-E-C-T
Take care of T.C.B. ♪

05:18.777 --> 05:21.612
♪ Oh, hey, baby ♪

05:21.697 --> 05:23.072
♪ Yeah ♪♪

05:23.156 --> 05:26.242
Hello. I'm Kurt Hummel,
and I'll be singing
"Mr. Cellophane."

05:26.326 --> 05:30.162
♪ Cellophane
Mr. Cellophane ♪

05:30.247 --> 05:34.166
♪ Should've been my name
Mr. Cellophane ♪

05:34.251 --> 05:36.669
♪ 'Cause you can
look right through me ♪

05:36.753 --> 05:38.796
♪ Walk right by me ♪

05:38.880 --> 05:42.550
♪ And never know I'm there ♪

05:42.634 --> 05:44.677
♪ Never even ♪

05:44.761 --> 05:52.727
♪ Know ♪

05:52.811 --> 05:55.438
♪ I'm there ♪♪

05:57.566 --> 06:01.318
[Girl]
Tina C.
"I Kissed a Girl."

06:01.403 --> 06:05.156
♪ It's not what I'm used to ♪

06:05.240 --> 06:08.367
♪Just wanna try you on ♪

06:08.452 --> 06:10.536
♪ I'm curious ♪

06:10.620 --> 06:14.790
♪ For you
caught my attention ♪

06:14.875 --> 06:18.419
♪ I kissed a girl
and liked it ♪♪

06:18.503 --> 06:20.463
[Bell Ringing]

06:20.547 --> 06:22.339
Hi.
My name is Rachel Berry,

06:22.424 --> 06:26.427
and I'll be singing "On My Own"
from the seminal
Broadway classic LesMis.

06:26.511 --> 06:28.220
Fantastic.
Let's hear it.

06:28.305 --> 06:31.182
♪ On my own ♪

06:31.266 --> 06:35.811
♪ Pretending he's beside me ♪♪

06:35.896 --> 06:38.314
[Rachel Narrating]
You might laugh because
every time I sign my name...

06:38.398 --> 06:40.399
I put a gold star after it.

06:40.484 --> 06:42.860
But it's a metaphor.
And metaphors are important.

06:42.944 --> 06:46.447
My gold stars are a metaphor
for me being a star.

06:52.329 --> 06:55.164
And just so we're clear,
I want to clear up
that hateful rumor...

06:55.248 --> 06:58.042
that I was the one
who turned that closet case
Sandy Ryerson in...

06:58.126 --> 07:00.461
because he gave Hank Saunders
the solo I deserved.

07:00.545 --> 07:01.796
That's cockapoopie.

07:01.880 --> 07:04.757
[Crying]
He was touching Hank,
caressing him.

07:04.841 --> 07:08.135
It was so wrong!

07:08.220 --> 07:11.180
[Crying Continues]

07:14.226 --> 07:17.686
[Narrating Resumes]
I am not homophobic.
In fact, I have two gay dads.

07:17.771 --> 07:19.522
See, I was born out of love.

07:19.606 --> 07:22.525
My two dads screened
potential surrogates
based on beauty and I.Q.

07:22.609 --> 07:25.986
Then they mixed
their sperm together
and used a turkey baster.

07:26.071 --> 07:28.239
To this day, we don't know
which one is my real dad,

07:28.323 --> 07:30.324
which I think is pretty amazing.

07:30.408 --> 07:32.576
My dads spoiled me in the arts.

07:32.661 --> 07:35.079
I was given dance lessons,
vocal lessons—

07:35.163 --> 07:37.623
anything to give me
a competitive edge.

07:41.545 --> 07:44.713
You might think
that all the boys in school
would totally want to tap this,

07:44.798 --> 07:48.801
but my MySpace schedule keeps me
way too busy to date.

07:48.885 --> 07:52.888
I try to post a MySpace video
every day just to keep my talent
alive and growing.

07:53.014 --> 07:57.685
♪ Without him ♪
Nowadays, being anonymous
is worse than being poor.

07:57.769 --> 08:00.563
Fame is the most important thing
in our culture now.

08:00.647 --> 08:04.150
And if there’s one thing
I've learned, it's that no one's
just gonna hand it to you.

08:04.234 --> 08:06.402
♪ I love him ♪

08:06.486 --> 08:11.323
♪ But every day
I'm learning ♪

08:11.408 --> 08:13.909
♪ All my life ♪
[Laughing]

08:13.994 --> 08:19.206
♪ I've only been pretending ♪

08:19.291 --> 08:25.087
♪ Without me
his world will go on turning ♪

08:25.172 --> 08:27.464
♪ A world that's full
of happiness ♪

08:27.549 --> 08:36.098
♪ That I have never known ♪

08:40.604 --> 08:42.605
♪ I love him ♪

08:45.901 --> 08:47.985
♪ I love him ♪

08:50.614 --> 08:54.241
♪ I love him ♪

08:54.326 --> 08:58.537
♪ But only on my ♪

08:58.622 --> 09:04.168
♪ Own ♪♪

09:04.252 --> 09:06.086
Very nice, Rachel.

09:06.171 --> 09:08.464
When do we start rehearsals?

09:08.548 --> 09:12.218
- ♪ And I said to myself, sit down ♪
- ♪ Said to myself, sit down ♪

09:12.302 --> 09:14.929
- ♪ Sit down
You're rockin' the boat ♪
- Bigger hands. Big hands.

09:15.013 --> 09:17.681
♪ Sit down
You're rockin' the boat ♪

09:17.766 --> 09:19.767
♪ And the devil
will drag you under ♪

09:19.851 --> 09:21.435
♪ By the sharp lapel
of your checkered coat ♪

09:21.519 --> 09:23.062
♪ Sit down, sit down
sit down, sit down ♪

09:23.146 --> 09:25.147
♪ Sit down
You're rockin' the boat ♪

09:25.232 --> 09:28.609
♪ Sit down, you're rockin'
Sit down, sit down, sit down
You're rockin' the boat ♪

09:28.693 --> 09:31.737
♪ Sit down, you're rockin'
Sit down, sit down, sit down
You're rockin' the boat ♪

09:31.821 --> 09:33.781
♪ Sit down ♪

09:33.865 --> 09:35.741
♪ You're rockin' ♪

09:35.825 --> 09:39.328
♪ The boat ♪♪

09:41.248 --> 09:44.208
- We suck.
- Uh- It—

09:44.292 --> 09:46.293
It'll get there.
We— We just need
to keep rehearsing.

09:46.378 --> 09:49.421
Mr. Schuester,
do you have any idea
how ridiculous it is to give...

09:49.506 --> 09:52.716
the lead solo in "Sit Down,
You're Rockin' the Boat"
to a boy in a wheelchair?

09:52.801 --> 09:55.636
I think
Mr. Schue's using irony
to enhance the performance.

09:55.720 --> 09:58.931
There's nothing ironic
about show choir!

10:01.059 --> 10:02.601
Rachel.

10:02.686 --> 10:03.686
Rachel!

10:03.770 --> 10:05.688
[Door Closes]

10:07.190 --> 10:09.316
That's sloppy!

10:09.401 --> 10:13.028
You're sloppy, babies!
It's just disgraceful!

10:13.113 --> 10:14.905
And I want the agony
out of your eyes!

10:14.990 --> 10:18.200
Uh-uh, Lance.
Don't you start crying!

10:18.285 --> 10:22.496
You are the weak link, pal!
How does it feel to be
the weak link, huh?

10:22.622 --> 10:25.499
That can't feel very good.
You changed
out of your costume.

10:25.583 --> 10:27.543
I'm tired of
being laughed at.

10:30.964 --> 10:33.882
You're the best kid
in there, Rachel.
That comes with a price.

10:33.967 --> 10:37.094
Look, I know I'm just
a sophomore. But I can feel
the clock ticking away,

10:37.178 --> 10:39.555
and I don't want
to leave high school
with nothing to show for it.

10:39.639 --> 10:41.932
You get great grades.
You're a fantastic singer.

10:42.017 --> 10:43.726
Everybody hates me.

10:43.810 --> 10:45.769
You think Glee Club
is gonna change that?

10:45.854 --> 10:48.147
Being great at something
is going to change it.

10:48.231 --> 10:51.442
Being a part
of something special
makes you special, right?

10:52.694 --> 10:54.862
I need a male lead
who can keep up with me vocally.

10:54.988 --> 10:57.156
Maybe I can coach
Artie a little. I—
Look, Mr. Schue,

10:57.240 --> 10:58.907
I appreciate what
you're trying to do.

10:58.992 --> 11:01.368
But if you can't give me
what I need, then I'm sorry.

11:01.453 --> 11:04.830
I'm not gonna make
a fool out of myself.

11:04.914 --> 11:07.291
I can't keep
wasting my time with Glee.

11:07.375 --> 11:09.668
It hurts too much.

11:09.753 --> 11:12.129
[Whistle Blows]
Schuester!

11:12.213 --> 11:14.089
Figgins wants ya!

11:17.927 --> 11:19.845
But we just started rehearsals.

11:19.929 --> 11:23.223
My hands are tied, Schue.
I need the auditorium.

11:23.308 --> 11:26.310
Alcoholics Anonymous
wants to rent it out
for their afternoon meetings.

11:26.394 --> 11:29.271
Lots of drunks in this town.
They're paying me
1 0 bucks a head.

11:29.356 --> 11:31.440
If we show at Regionals,
Glee stays.

11:31.524 --> 11:33.442
If not, the bar is open
in the auditorium.

11:33.526 --> 11:36.528
What is it
with you and this club?
You've got only five kids.

11:36.613 --> 11:39.823
- One of them's a cripple!
- Then I guess you've got
nothing to worry about.

11:39.908 --> 11:41.450
[Sighs]

11:42.744 --> 11:45.829
- Fine.
- Yes!
[Chuckles]

11:45.914 --> 11:48.665
But you're running detention
for free to make it up to me.

11:50.794 --> 11:53.170
Deal.

11:56.257 --> 11:58.384
You put your hands
in the corners like this.

11:58.510 --> 12:00.928
Okay?
I can't do it.

12:01.012 --> 12:02.638
I'm dyslexic.

12:02.722 --> 12:05.808
Maybe I should just stick to
towels and washcloths.

12:05.892 --> 12:08.894
Howard, if you can't fold
a fitted sheet, you cannot
work at Sheets 'N' Things.

12:08.978 --> 12:11.397
[Bell Dings]
[Man]
Associate return.

12:11.481 --> 12:14.233
Go. Make sure
they have a receipt.

12:16.027 --> 12:18.946
Someone looks beautiful
today. Hi.

12:19.072 --> 12:21.198
You look very handsome.
Thank you.

12:22.492 --> 12:24.284
Roast beef on pumpernickel.
Your favorite.
Ohh!

12:24.411 --> 12:26.620
Oh, does it have mayo?
Yeah.

12:26.704 --> 12:29.540
Will, if my diabetes comes back,
I can't get pregnant.

12:29.666 --> 12:31.792
I-
What is wrong with you?

12:31.876 --> 12:33.794
[Sighs]
Well, I wanted
to tell you...

12:33.878 --> 12:37.047
that I'm gonna
have to start workin' late
for the next couple months.

12:37.173 --> 12:39.925
I'm, uh, monitoring
after-school detention.
What?

12:40.009 --> 12:42.928
I had to make a deal
with Figgins so he wouldn't
kill Glee Club.

12:43.012 --> 12:46.014
But, Will, I'm on my feet
four hours a day,
three times a week here.

12:46.099 --> 12:48.642
Now I have to go home
and I have to cook dinner
for myself?

12:48.768 --> 12:51.854
[Scoffs]
This lady wants to
return these sheets.

12:51.938 --> 12:54.982
But something tells me
we've got another
bed wetter.

12:55.066 --> 13:00.070
[Sighs]
Do you see what I have to
deal with here, hmm?

13:01.156 --> 13:02.906
God, hasn't she ever
heard of a diaper?

13:02.991 --> 13:06.326
[Sandy]
Of course towels
have a thread count, Mr...

13:06.411 --> 13:08.537
Sheets 'N' Things!

13:08.621 --> 13:11.707
What do you do?
I read catalogs!
I know these things.

13:11.791 --> 13:15.794
Anything under
a 400-thread count and
I could break out in impetigo!

13:15.879 --> 13:19.047
It's simple to understand!
William?

13:19.132 --> 13:21.049
Sandy? Hey!

13:21.134 --> 13:23.760
Well, hello.
How are things?

13:23.845 --> 13:26.597
I hear you have
taken over Glee Club.

13:26.681 --> 13:29.475
Yeah.
I hope you're not too upset.

13:29.559 --> 13:32.060
Are you kidding?
Getting out of that
swirling eddy of despair-

13:32.145 --> 13:34.021
best thing that ever
happened to me.

13:34.147 --> 13:35.939
[Whistles]
[Chuckles]

13:36.024 --> 13:39.026
Don't get me wrong.
It wasn't easy at first.

13:39.110 --> 13:41.987
Being dismissed.
And for what I was
accused of?

13:42.071 --> 13:45.616
My long-distance girlfriend
in Cleveland nearly
broke up with me.

13:45.700 --> 13:48.243
Oh, God. Don't you
love a good monkey?

13:48.328 --> 13:51.038
It took me weeks to get over
my nervous breakdown.

13:51.164 --> 13:54.583
Did they put you
on medication?
Better. Medical marijuana.

13:54.667 --> 13:56.835
It's genius!

13:56.920 --> 13:59.713
I just tell my Dr. Feelgood
I'm having trouble sleeping,

13:59.797 --> 14:02.299
and he gives me
all of it I want.

14:02.383 --> 14:04.593
I'm finding
the whole system
quite lucrative.

14:04.719 --> 14:08.597
You're a drug dealer?
Oh, yeah. Make five times more
than when I was a teacher.

14:08.681 --> 14:12.935
I keep some for myself
and then I take
money baths in the rest.

14:13.019 --> 14:14.728
Who-Who do you sell it to?

14:19.442 --> 14:22.277
You want in?

14:22.362 --> 14:24.279
Uh, no.
[Chuckles]
I tried it once in college.

14:24.364 --> 14:26.240
But Terri and I are
trying to get pregnant.

14:26.366 --> 14:28.575
I do my own packaging.
Sandy, no—

14:28.660 --> 14:30.452
And the first sample
is free. Come on.

14:30.537 --> 14:33.705
You are the one coaching
those tone-deaf acne factories.
You're gonna need it.

14:33.790 --> 14:36.458
What?
This looks like barf.

14:36.543 --> 14:38.794
Okay? I have to
do everything myself.

14:38.878 --> 14:40.879
Call me.
Come on.

14:40.964 --> 14:44.675
What's the matter
with you?
Scary.

14:44.759 --> 14:48.303
[Knocking]
Hey, Sue.
C-Can I have a sec?

14:50.348 --> 14:52.182
Sure, buddy. Come on in.

14:56.646 --> 14:59.940
Eew!
[Gasping]

15:01.734 --> 15:03.819
Hey, Emma.
You got a second?

15:03.903 --> 15:05.862
- What is that? Gum?
- Uh-huh.

15:05.947 --> 15:08.574
So you want to talk
to my Cheerios
about joining Glee Club?

15:08.658 --> 15:10.367
Well, I need more kids-
Performers.

15:10.451 --> 15:12.536
And all the best ones
are in the Cheerios.

15:12.620 --> 15:14.538
I figured some of them
might want to double up.

15:14.622 --> 15:18.166
Okay.
So what you're doing right now
is called blurring the lines.

15:18.251 --> 15:21.712
High school is a caste system.
Kids fall into certain slots.

15:21.796 --> 15:25.549
Your jocks,
your popular kids,
up in the penthouse.

15:25.633 --> 15:30.470
The invisibles and the kids
playing live-action druids
and trolls out in the forest,

15:30.555 --> 15:32.472
bottom floor.

15:32.557 --> 15:34.600
And... where do
the Glee kids lie?

15:34.684 --> 15:36.810
Sub-basement.

15:36.894 --> 15:39.730
Sue's not wrong.
But I don't think anything's
set in stone.

15:39.814 --> 15:44.026
I mean, kids are gonna do
what they think is cool, which
is not always who they are.

15:44.152 --> 15:47.446
You just need to find a way to
get them out of their boxes.
Well, how do I do that?

15:47.530 --> 15:50.699
They follow the leader.
If you can get a couple of
the popular kids to sign up,

15:50.783 --> 15:52.409
the rest will fall
right in line.

15:52.535 --> 15:55.454
I just want to
talk to them.
I don't know, dude.

15:55.538 --> 15:58.206
I can't see any of my guys
wanting to join the Glee Club.

15:58.291 --> 16:00.709
Last month, they held down
one of their teammates,
shaved off his eyebrows...

16:00.793 --> 16:02.711
just because he
watched Grey's Anatomy.

16:02.795 --> 16:06.423
Look, all I'm looking for
is an introduction.
Fine.

16:06.507 --> 16:09.593
You gotta put a good word
in for me with Emma.

16:10.803 --> 16:15.057
- There you go, Cinderella.
- Thank you.

16:15.141 --> 16:19.645
I have trouble
with things like that.
The, um- The messy things.

16:19.729 --> 16:21.688
Yeah.

16:21.773 --> 16:23.857
It's really nice
how much you care about Glee.

16:23.941 --> 16:26.068
About the kids.
[Bell Rings]

16:26.152 --> 16:29.279
If you really care about
these kids, you'll leave
well enough alone.

16:29.364 --> 16:31.198
Children like to know
where they stand.

16:31.282 --> 16:34.159
So let your little Glee kids
have their little club.

16:34.243 --> 16:37.996
But don't pretend
that any of them
are something they're not.

16:38.081 --> 16:40.040
[Buzzing]

16:44.462 --> 16:46.755
[Whistle Blows]
Circle up!

16:46.839 --> 16:49.132
Now Mr. Schuester
is gonna talk to you.

16:49.217 --> 16:53.595
You don't listen, you do laps.
You mouth off, you do laps.

16:53.680 --> 16:55.931
Got it?
They're all yours, Will.

16:56.015 --> 16:58.016
Thanks, Ken.
Hey, guys. How you doing?

16:58.101 --> 17:02.604
I think I recognize some of you
from Spanish class.
But, uh, I'm—

17:02.689 --> 17:05.691
I'm here today to talk to you
about something different.
Uh, music.

17:05.775 --> 17:07.651
[Chuckles Nervously]

17:09.779 --> 17:11.905
Glee Club needs guys.

17:11.989 --> 17:13.907
I can sing.

17:13.991 --> 17:16.034
Really? That's fantastic.

17:16.119 --> 17:18.453
- You wanna hear?
- Yeah.

17:18.538 --> 17:20.455
[Chuckles]

17:20.540 --> 17:23.917
[Cheering]

17:27.672 --> 17:29.506
- [Farts]
- [Laughing]

17:29.590 --> 17:32.300
Oh, yeah!

17:34.011 --> 17:36.304
[Mouths Words]
Laps.
[Chattering]

17:38.307 --> 17:41.393
I'm gonna put the sign-up sheet
at the door. So if anyone
wants to sign up, please—

17:41.519 --> 17:43.687
Thank you.
[Whistle Blows]

17:43.771 --> 17:46.106
[Ken]
Dismissed! Puck, in my office
in five minutes.

17:48.609 --> 17:52.112
You been sleeping okay?
Your eyes look
a little bloodshot.

17:52.196 --> 17:54.698
I got allergies.

17:54.782 --> 17:57.826
Okay, buddy.
Thanks again.

18:00.037 --> 18:03.373
[Shower Running]

18:03.458 --> 18:06.126
[Will Narrating]
I honestly thought that was
the end of the very brief...

18:06.210 --> 18:08.837
fever dream
that was New Directions.

18:08.921 --> 18:13.759
[Boy]
♪ Even as I wander
I'm keepin' you in sight ♪

18:13.843 --> 18:16.261
♪ You're a candle
in the window ♪

18:16.345 --> 18:19.097
♪ On a cold, dark
winter's night ♪

18:19.182 --> 18:27.063
♪ And I'm getting closer
than I ever thought I might ♪

18:27.148 --> 18:31.067
[Imitating Drumming]
♪ And I can't fight
this feelin' anymore ♪

18:31.152 --> 18:34.404
I suddenly realized why
I had wanted to do this thing
in the first place.

18:34.489 --> 18:37.866
♪ I'd forgotten what
I'd started fighting for ♪

18:37.950 --> 18:41.077
It was seeing
the gift in a kid that
they didn't even know they had.

18:41.162 --> 18:43.914
♪ And I can't fight
this feelin' anymore ♪

18:43.998 --> 18:46.875
It was pure talent.

18:46.959 --> 18:49.211
♪ If I have to crawl
upon your floor ♪

18:49.295 --> 18:52.088
♪ Come crashing
through your door ♪

18:52.173 --> 18:55.926
♪ Baby, I can't
fight this feelin' anymore ♪♪

18:56.010 --> 19:00.722
What I did then was
the blackest moment of my life.

19:02.558 --> 19:05.560
You want to tell me
how long you've had
a drug problem?

19:05.645 --> 19:07.604
I don't even know
who the chronic lady is.

19:07.688 --> 19:11.650
Look, if it were up to me,
we wouldn't have mandatory
biweekly locker checks.

19:11.734 --> 19:13.693
But I've never seen that
before, Mr. Schue.
I swear. It's not mine!

19:13.778 --> 19:15.862
I'll pee in a cup!

19:15.947 --> 19:18.782
- I'll pee.
- Look, it wouldn't
make any difference.

19:18.866 --> 19:21.535
Possession is
eight-tenths of the law.

19:21.619 --> 19:25.539
I'm pretty sure that much pot
is a felony. Yeah.

19:25.623 --> 19:27.791
Look, you'll get kicked
out of school.

19:27.875 --> 19:29.376
You'll lose your
football scholarship.

19:29.460 --> 19:32.379
Wait, I-
I had a football scholarship?
To-To where?

19:32.505 --> 19:35.090
You could land in prison,
son.
Oh, my God.

19:35.174 --> 19:38.260
Please, don't tell my mom.

19:38.344 --> 19:42.514
[Sighs]
Look, I see a lot of myself
in you, Finn.

19:42.598 --> 19:47.018
I know what it's like
to struggle to make
good life choices.

19:47.103 --> 19:50.438
And I don't want to see you
throw away everything
you have to offer the world.

19:53.025 --> 19:55.485
I just expected
more out of you, Finn.

19:55.570 --> 19:58.488
[Finn Narrating]
That really got to me
when Mr. Schuester said that.

19:58.573 --> 20:02.367
Because every day of my life,
I expect more out of myself.

20:02.451 --> 20:04.369
See, I might look confident
and everything.

20:04.453 --> 20:08.623
But I really struggle with
the same thing other kids do.
Peer pressure, backne.

20:10.585 --> 20:16.423
I never knew my dad. He died
in Iraq when we were fighting
Osama bin Laden the first time.

20:17.633 --> 20:20.093
Hold on, hold on.
Finn! Finn! Finn!

20:20.177 --> 20:22.095
Please! I'm on the phone.

20:22.179 --> 20:25.098
I just want to trade
next Saturday's shift
for this Saturday...

20:25.182 --> 20:26.933
because Finn's got
a parents' night for Cub Scouts.

20:27.018 --> 20:29.394
[Narrating Continues]
My mom and me, we're real close.

20:29.478 --> 20:31.396
But being a single parent
can be hard.

20:31.480 --> 20:36.693
The only good time for Mom was
when we splurged a little bit
and ordered Emerald Dreams.

20:36.777 --> 20:38.737
Darren was good to her.

20:38.821 --> 20:40.989
And he was cool about
letting me hang out.

20:43.451 --> 20:47.120
♪ You make me weep ♪

20:48.873 --> 20:51.791
♪ And wanna die ♪

20:51.918 --> 20:55.879
♪Just when- ♪
That was the first time
I really "heard" music.

20:55.963 --> 20:57.881
♪ You said we'd try ♪

20:57.965 --> 21:01.134
♪ Lovin', touchin' ♪

21:01.260 --> 21:05.847
♪ Squeezin' ♪
Man, it set my soul on fire.

21:05.932 --> 21:08.266
♪ Each other ♪

21:08.351 --> 21:11.186
You got a voice, buddy.

21:11.270 --> 21:15.065
Seriously, if I had
that voice, my band would
still be together.

21:16.484 --> 21:18.610
Stick with it!

21:18.694 --> 21:23.406
My mom took it real hard when
Darren left her for that girl
he met at Pic 'N' Save.

21:23.491 --> 21:26.117
[Man]
♪ With someone else ♪

21:26.202 --> 21:30.747
♪ Lovin', touchin', squeezin' ♪

21:30.831 --> 21:32.749
[Shouts, Indistinct]

21:32.833 --> 21:35.752
♪ Each other ♪

21:35.836 --> 21:39.673
♪ Now it's your turn, girl
to cry ♪

21:39.757 --> 21:42.926
♪ Na, na, na-na-na-na ♪

21:43.010 --> 21:47.055
It was at that moment I decided
to do whatever it took
to make my mom proud of me,

21:47.139 --> 21:49.933
make her feel
all her sacrifice was worth it.

21:50.017 --> 21:51.851
[Will]
We have two options here.

21:51.936 --> 21:55.480
I'm running detention now,
so you can do six weeks
after school.

21:55.564 --> 21:58.566
But that's gonna remain
on your permanent record.

21:59.777 --> 22:02.153
What's the other option,
Mr. Schue?

22:02.238 --> 22:04.364
♪♪ [Piano]

22:04.448 --> 22:09.452
♪ I got chills
They're multiplyin' ♪

22:09.537 --> 22:13.164
♪ And I'm losin' control ♪

22:13.249 --> 22:18.461
♪ 'Cause the power
you're supplyin' ♪

22:18.546 --> 22:20.171
♪ It's electrifyin' ♪

22:20.256 --> 22:22.298
- ♪ You better shape up ♪
- ♪ Doo, doo, doo ♪

22:22.383 --> 22:25.677
- ♪ 'Cause I need a man ♪
- ♪ Doo, doo, doo ♪

22:25.761 --> 22:28.972
- ♪ But my heart is set on you ♪
- ♪ And my heart is set on you ♪

22:29.056 --> 22:33.435
♪ You better shape up
You better understand ♪

22:34.437 --> 22:36.354
♪ To my heart I must be true ♪

22:36.439 --> 22:40.442
- ♪ Nothin' left ♪
- ♪ Nothin' left for me to do ♪

22:40.526 --> 22:44.779
- ♪ You're the one that I want ♪
- ♪ You are the one I want
Ooh, ooh, ooh, honey ♪

22:44.864 --> 22:47.532
- ♪ The one that I want ♪♪
- Oh, hell to the no!

22:47.616 --> 22:50.368
Look, I'm not down with this
background singing nonsense!

22:50.453 --> 22:52.829
I'm Beyoncé!
I ain't no Kelly Rowland.

22:52.913 --> 22:55.498
Okay, look, Mercedes.
It's just one song.

22:55.583 --> 22:57.959
And it's the first time
we've been kind of good.

22:59.170 --> 23:02.630
Okay. You're good, white boy.
I'll give you that.

23:02.715 --> 23:05.967
But you better bring it.
Let's run it again.

23:06.052 --> 23:08.595
All right. Let's do it.
From the top.

23:11.390 --> 23:13.641
You usually don't let me
in your craft room.

23:13.726 --> 23:16.478
Isn't this fun?
And challenging?

23:16.562 --> 23:18.480
Every Wednesday
we're gonna have puzzle night...

23:18.564 --> 23:21.983
because I know how important
it is for you to have
a creative outlet.

23:22.068 --> 23:24.319
[Sighs]

23:25.821 --> 23:27.739
You know, the kids
have been working so hard.

23:27.823 --> 23:30.742
I was thinking about taking them
on a field trip next Saturday.

23:30.826 --> 23:32.911
Carmel High's performing
a showcase down in Akron.

23:32.995 --> 23:35.246
Carmel's gonna be the team
to beat at Regionals,

23:35.331 --> 23:38.625
and I was wondering if you might
want to come chaperone with me.

23:38.751 --> 23:42.462
On Saturday?
Oh, I can't.
Oh.

23:42.546 --> 23:45.882
I had to pick up an extra shift
at work, Will. We're living
paycheck to paycheck.

23:45.966 --> 23:48.927
How much of that paycheck
goes to your Pottery Barn
credit card?

23:49.011 --> 23:52.055
I don't know
what you're talking about.

23:53.307 --> 23:54.474
Don't go in
the Christmas closet!

23:54.558 --> 23:57.435
I was looking for my jacket
the other day. Come on!

23:57.520 --> 24:01.356
- We cannot afford this stuff, Terri!
- But we could, Will!

24:01.440 --> 24:05.318
Yes, I am a shoo-in to be
promoted during the Christmas
week at Sheets 'N' Things!

24:05.402 --> 24:09.155
I reek of management potential!
And they're hiring
at H.W. Menken!

24:09.240 --> 24:12.826
My passion is teaching, Terri!
For the last time, I don't
want to be an accountant!

24:12.910 --> 24:17.247
Dr. Phil said people could
change. It's not a bad thing
to want a real life, Will.

24:17.331 --> 24:19.791
And to have a glue gun
that works!

24:23.129 --> 24:27.006
You know, it's really hard
for me not having
the things that I need.

24:27.091 --> 24:30.593
Oh! And you need
three mahogany
toilet brush holders?

24:30.678 --> 24:32.720
They're Balinese!

24:32.805 --> 24:37.267
It is not a bad thing
to want things, Will.

24:38.477 --> 24:41.062
I understand your interest
in these kids, Will.

24:41.147 --> 24:43.731
I really do.
Yeah.

24:43.816 --> 24:46.943
It's your way of
recapturing your glory days.

24:47.027 --> 24:49.154
But I'm not
the high school cheerleader
anymore...

24:49.238 --> 24:51.156
and you are
not the golden boy.

24:51.240 --> 24:54.409
High school's over
for both of us.

24:55.870 --> 24:58.288
It's time that you move on.

25:05.254 --> 25:08.256
[Motor Whirring]

25:44.877 --> 25:46.419
[Chuckling]

25:46.503 --> 25:48.046
[Ken]
You're the quarterback!

25:48.172 --> 25:50.715
Coach, it's temporary—
No!
I don't want to hear it!

25:50.799 --> 25:53.426
You make a decision.
Either you’re a football player
or you're a singer!

25:55.763 --> 25:58.097
Hey, what's going on?

25:58.182 --> 26:01.351
Oh, it's— I just-
I have to miss practice
Saturday afternoon.

26:01.435 --> 26:05.355
It's, uh, my mom.
I gotta help her cook
and, uh, do things.

26:05.439 --> 26:07.357
Why?

26:07.441 --> 26:09.359
She just had,
uh, surgery.

26:09.443 --> 26:11.361
What kind of surgery?

26:11.445 --> 26:15.073
Uh, well, she, uh, had to
have her prostate out.

26:15.157 --> 26:17.075
Man,
that's a tough break.

26:17.159 --> 26:19.160
Yeah.
It's, uh, engorged.

26:20.746 --> 26:23.623
You think this is hard?
I'm living with hepatitis.
That's hard!

26:25.793 --> 26:28.544
You stole my quarterback.

26:28.629 --> 26:31.714
Okay, look,
Finn's got a great voice.

26:31.799 --> 26:33.675
He just wants
to express himself.

26:33.801 --> 26:37.428
You're screwing up my life.
Okay, Ken?
You hate football.

26:37.554 --> 26:39.639
What's this really about?
[Bell Ringing]

26:41.475 --> 26:43.184
Hey, M&M.

26:43.269 --> 26:46.688
So, I got tickets
to monster trucks
this weekend.

26:46.814 --> 26:49.691
Loge tickets.
No, thanks.
Not my thing.

26:49.775 --> 26:53.611
Truckzilla vs. Truckosaurus.
And get this—
the trucks breathe fire.

26:53.696 --> 26:57.490
Ken, look, you know
how every time you ask me out,
I tell you I'm on my period?

26:57.616 --> 27:00.660
Which doesn't bother me.
Or I tell you I'm suffering
from cluster headaches.

27:00.744 --> 27:02.745
Or I'm allergic to nighttime.

27:02.830 --> 27:04.831
Those things?
Not really true.

27:04.957 --> 27:07.667
I'm just not interested
in dating you—
Shh.

27:09.211 --> 27:12.297
How do I get you...
into my hatchback?

27:12.381 --> 27:15.341
Okay, Ken, fine. Make me say it.
I like somebody else.

27:15.426 --> 27:19.887
Nothing I can do about it
because they're unavailable, so
I have to deal with that, but-

27:21.223 --> 27:23.224
[Gasps]

27:23.309 --> 27:25.101
[Bell Rings]

27:25.185 --> 27:27.603
You're right.
I'm overreacting.

27:27.688 --> 27:30.148
- The herd
will take care of it.
- The herd?

27:30.232 --> 27:31.983
The student body.

27:32.067 --> 27:35.903
The second someone tries
to rise above, be different,
herd pulls 'em back in.

27:35.988 --> 27:38.239
So-
Oh, and by the way,

27:38.324 --> 27:41.826
thanks for
putting a good word in
for me with Emma, buddy.

27:41.910 --> 27:44.746
I guess you just want her
for yourself, huh?

27:46.248 --> 27:48.624
Adios, amigo.

27:53.756 --> 27:56.215
You're very talented.
Really?

27:56.300 --> 27:58.217
Yeah.

27:58.302 --> 28:01.095
I would know.
I'm very talented too.

28:02.473 --> 28:05.600
I think the rest of the team
expects us to become an item.

28:05.684 --> 28:07.602
You, the hot male lead,

28:07.686 --> 28:11.356
and me, the stunning young ingenue
everyone roots for.

28:11.440 --> 28:14.233
Well, I, uh,
have a girlfriend.

28:14.318 --> 28:16.736
Really? Who?

28:16.820 --> 28:18.738
Quinn Fabray.

28:18.822 --> 28:20.740
Cheerleader Quinn Fabray?

28:20.824 --> 28:22.909
The president
of the celibacy club?

28:32.503 --> 28:34.170
Wait.

28:37.716 --> 28:39.967
Let's pray.

28:40.052 --> 28:42.720
[Female Singer]
♪ Oh, no-no-no-no-no-no ♪

28:42.805 --> 28:46.265
For almost
four months now.
She's cool.

28:46.350 --> 28:49.519
I wonder if they have
Sour Patch Kids.

28:50.813 --> 28:53.815
Those kielbasas look like
they've been there a while.

28:53.899 --> 28:56.776
Do you want to go halfsies
on a P.B. and J.?

28:56.902 --> 28:58.528
That sounds perfect.
Yeah?

28:58.612 --> 29:00.238
Yeah.
Let's go.

29:00.322 --> 29:02.156
Sorry.
Excuse me.

29:02.241 --> 29:06.494
I haven't had a peanut butter
and jelly sandwich in...
a really long time.

29:06.620 --> 29:08.913
Really?
Yeah. My wife's
allergic to nuts.

29:08.997 --> 29:11.999
Oh. Oh. Well, that's
really sweet though.

29:12.084 --> 29:13.960
Not eating something
because she can't.

29:14.086 --> 29:15.628
Oh. Yeah.
It's very nice.

29:15.712 --> 29:17.588
[Foil Crinkling]
Oh, that's
really noisy.

29:17.714 --> 29:19.340
But they're clean.
[Laughs]

29:19.466 --> 29:21.134
Oh, my gosh.
There you go.

29:21.260 --> 29:22.802
How, um-
Mmm.

29:22.886 --> 29:24.595
How long have you two
been married?

29:24.680 --> 29:26.305
Mmm, five years
last March.

29:26.390 --> 29:27.974
Really? Mmm.
Yeah.

29:28.058 --> 29:29.976
But we've been together
since high school.

29:30.060 --> 29:31.978
She was my first girlfriend,
actually.

29:32.062 --> 29:33.980
Was it love
at first sight?

29:34.064 --> 29:35.940
For me it was.

29:36.024 --> 29:39.652
I don't know.
She used to be filled
with so much joy.

29:39.778 --> 29:42.155
And now?
[Bell Dinging]

29:42.239 --> 29:44.907
Ah, showtime.
[Chuckles]

29:45.033 --> 29:47.952
You don't want to hear about
my marital problems.
No, I do.

29:48.036 --> 29:52.081
I do— I'd love to hear—
You— I'm not happy that
you have marital problems.

29:52.207 --> 29:55.585
People talk to me a lot because
I'm a guidance counselor.
Okay, here's the thing.

29:55.711 --> 29:58.629
Terri rides me hard,
and I've always appreciated it.
Mm-hmm.

29:58.714 --> 30:01.632
I figure she just wants me
to be better, you know?

30:01.717 --> 30:04.635
But lately, though,
I keep asking myself,
better at what?

30:04.720 --> 30:07.638
Making money?
Being upwardly mobile?
Thank you.

30:07.723 --> 30:10.600
[Sighs]
I don't know. I love her.
Don't get me wrong.

30:10.726 --> 30:13.644
But we just gotta
get back on the same page.
Did you like the sandwich?

30:13.729 --> 30:16.230
Oh, my God.
It's, like, the best
I've ever had.

30:16.315 --> 30:19.400
Hey, guys.
So this is supposed to be
our "competition."

30:19.485 --> 30:22.487
But I honestly don't think
that they've got the talent
that we've got.

30:22.571 --> 30:25.406
But let's be a good audience.
Give them some of that old
McKinley High respect.

30:25.491 --> 30:27.700
[Announcer]
Please give a warm
Buckeye State welcome...

30:27.784 --> 30:33.414
to last year's
regional champion,
Vocal Adrenaline!

30:40.255 --> 30:42.632
♪ Ohio ♪

30:42.716 --> 30:44.967
♪ Ohio ♪

30:45.052 --> 30:50.598
♪ Ohio ♪

30:50.682 --> 30:53.100
♪ They tried to make me
go to rehab ♪

30:53.185 --> 30:56.771
♪ But I said no, no, no ♪

30:56.855 --> 30:59.607
♪ Yes, I've been black
but when I come back ♪

30:59.691 --> 31:01.275
♪ You'll know, know, know ♪

31:02.402 --> 31:05.363
♪ I ain't got the time ♪

31:05.447 --> 31:08.449
♪ And if my daddy
thinks I'm fine ♪

31:08.534 --> 31:10.368
♪ He'll try to make me go
to rehab ♪

31:10.452 --> 31:13.162
- [Audience Cheering]
